transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hi, Andrew.

Speaker 1: Yeah, this is Juan Sifuni.

Speaker 2: I received a package in the mail today.

Speaker 1: I didn't order it.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Let me take a look here.

Speaker 2: I didn't even open it up yet.

Speaker 1: Yeah, Mr. Sifuni?

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: And I looked at my Discover card, and I see it for another $63.95.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay, so from what I can see here, I'm looking at your account.

Speaker 2: I think what happened, because you ordered ten, so the doctor wrote your

Speaker 1: prescription with refills.

Speaker 2: But if you don't need refills, what I can do,

Speaker 1: I can tell the pharmacy to stop the initial writing from physicians

Speaker 2: who pause the prescription.

Speaker 1: So you can just order as needed.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Did you not open that one?

Speaker 2: No, I didn't open the first one.

Speaker 1: Okay, so if you want,

Speaker 2: you can write refuse return to the sender on that package, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And then I'm going to pause the prescription so you can try what you have

Speaker 1: first, okay?

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: So are they going to cancel on my credit card,

Speaker 2: or do I get to call Discover card?

Speaker 1: So when you write refuse return to the sender,

Speaker 2: that's what I say for your refund, right,

Speaker 1: for that one that you wasn't ready.

Speaker 2: And I'm going to tell the doctor that you're not a really active patient,

Speaker 1: so you don't need every 30 days.

Speaker 2: So they're going to pause the prescription for you.

Speaker 1: I think they pause it for half a year so you can reorder yourself,

Speaker 2: but you're not on a monthly anymore because you're not active, okay?

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: So I just want to write return to sender on this package?

Speaker 1: That's it.

Speaker 2: Leave it in your mailbox.

Speaker 1: Mailman's going to take that for you, okay?

Speaker 2: And I'm pausing the prescription here for you,

Speaker 1: and you get your refund, 63.95, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, 63.95.

Speaker 1: And when will I see that refund?

Speaker 2: It takes five to ten business days usually,

Speaker 1: but it could be sooner based on the bank that you have.

Speaker 2: The bank tells us to say five to ten to be safe, basically.

Speaker 1: So I'm pausing that prescription.

Speaker 2: And then, yeah, just write refuse return, put it back in the mailbox,

Speaker 1: and then you get your refund.

Speaker 2: I'm starting the refund here, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: All right, so I should see a refund.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you can leave it in the mailbox when you put it back.

Speaker 2: Well, that's what I'm going to do.

Speaker 1: Yeah, mm-hmm.

Speaker 2: All right, so I'm going to –

Speaker 1: And those business days, five to ten to be safe.

Speaker 2: It could be sooner depending on your bank.

Speaker 1: I'm not sure which bank is doing what, but five to ten, you will get it, okay?

Speaker 2: Yeah, it was on a Discover card.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you get your refund, okay?

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, so on the way back then.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
